# Component Rules for Plutony Web Project

## Centralized Components & Styles

### MANDATORY: Use Existing Centralized Components

**CRITICAL: Before creating any new UI component, ALWAYS check and use existing centralized components:**

#### Available Centralized Components

**From `@/app/ui/components/`:**

- **`CircularIcon`** - For all circular gradient icons with variants (primary, secondary, accent, blue, diagonal, reverse)
- **`SectionBadge`** - For section header badges with consistent styling
- **`SectionDivider`** - For gradient divider lines between sections
- **`GlassButton`** - For buttons with glass morphism effects
- **`StandardCard`** - For cards with glass effects and hover animations
- **`StandardSection`** - For section wrappers with consistent backgrounds

**From `@/app/lib/design-system.ts`:**

- **`badgeVariants`** - Badge styling variants
- **`circularIconVariants`** - Circular icon styling with animations
- **`cardVariants`** - Card styling with glass effects
- **`buttonVariants`** - Button styling variants
- **`sectionVariants`** - Section background variants
- **`dividerVariants`** - Gradient divider styling

### Component Usage Rules

**‚úÖ ALWAYS DO:**

```typescript
// Use centralized components
import { CircularIcon, SectionBadge, StandardCard } from '@/app/ui/components'

// Use existing variants from design system
import { circularIconVariants } from '@/lib/design-system'

// Example: Creating a feature card
<StandardCard variant="glass" className="hover:scale-105">
  <CircularIcon icon={Star} variant="primary" size="lg" />
  <SectionBadge variant="primary">New Feature</SectionBadge>
</StandardCard>
```

**‚ùå NEVER DO:**

```typescript
// Don't recreate existing patterns manually
<div className="bg-white/10 backdrop-blur-md rounded-2xl border border-white/20 shadow-xl hover:shadow-2xl transition-all duration-300 hover:scale-105">
  <div className="w-16 h-16 bg-gradient-to-br from-blue-500 to-purple-600 rounded-full flex items-center justify-center">
    <Star className="w-8 h-8 text-white" />
  </div>
  <span className="px-3 py-1 bg-gradient-to-r from-blue-500 to-purple-600 text-white text-sm font-medium rounded-full">
    New Feature
  </span>
</div>
```

### Before Creating New Components

**MANDATORY CHECKLIST:**

1. **Check existing components** in `@/ui/components/` and `@/lib/design-system.ts`
2. **Search for similar patterns** in the codebase using semantic search
3. **Extend existing components** rather than creating new ones
4. **Ask for approval** before creating new components if existing ones can be extended

### Extending Existing Components

**Preferred approach:**

```typescript
// Extend existing component with new variant
const circularIconVariants = cva(
  "existing-base-classes",
  {
    variants: {
      variant: {
        // ... existing variants
        newVariant: "new-variant-classes" // Add new variant
      }
    }
  }
)

// Or create composed component
const SpecialCard = ({ children, ...props }) => (
  <StandardCard variant="glass" {...props}>
    <div className="special-additional-styling">
      {children}
    </div>
  </StandardCard>
)
```

### Common Patterns to Avoid

**These patterns are already centralized - use the components instead:**

- Glass morphism effects (`backdrop-blur-md`, `bg-white/10`)
- Circular gradient icons (`bg-gradient-to-br`, `rounded-full`)
- Hover animations (`hover:scale-105`, `transition-all duration-300`)
- Card containers with shadows and borders
- Section badges with gradient backgrounds
- Gradient divider lines
- Glass buttons with hover effects

## üé® Tailwind CSS Best Practices

### Component-First Approach

- Extract repeated Tailwind classes into reusable components
- Use CVA (Class Variance Authority) for component variants
- Follow mobile-first responsive design principles
- Use Tailwind's design tokens consistently

### Styling Guidelines

```typescript
// Good: Component with variants
const Button = cva("base-button-classes", {
  variants: {
    variant: {
      primary: "bg-blue-600 text-white",
      secondary: "bg-gray-200 text-gray-900"
    },
    size: {
      sm: "px-3 py-1.5 text-sm",
      md: "px-4 py-2 text-base"
    }
  }
})

// Bad: Inline repeated classes
<button className="px-4 py-2 bg-blue-600 text-white rounded-md hover:bg-blue-700">
```

### Design System

- Use consistent spacing scale (4, 8, 12, 16, 20, 24, 32, 40, 48, 64)
- Follow established color palette
- Maintain consistent typography hierarchy
- Use semantic color names in Tailwind config

